# Kolekto - Smart Group Payment Platform

## Project Overview
Kolekto is a React-based web application for facilitating group payments. It allows organizers to create payment collections and share links/QR codes for contributors to pay without creating accounts.

## Tech Stack
- React 18 + TypeScript + Vite
- Tailwind CSS + shadcn/ui components
- Zustand for state management
- Supabase for backend
- Paystack for payments
- React Router DOM for routing
- React Hook Form + Zod for forms
- TanStack Query for data fetching

## Key Features
- Group payment collection
- QR code generation
- Multiple payment methods (Opay, Flutterwave, cards, bank transfers)
- Real-time payment confirmations
- No account required for contributors
- Bulk payments for multiple people

## File Structure
- `/src/components/` - Reusable UI components
- `/src/pages/` - Page components
- `/src/context/` - React context providers
- `/src/store/` - Zustand state management
- `/src/components/ui/` - shadcn/ui components
- `/src/components/home/` - Landing page components

## Development Guidelines
- Use TypeScript for all new files
- Follow shadcn/ui component patterns
- Use Tailwind CSS for styling
- Implement proper error handling
- Follow React best practices
- Use Zustand for global state management
- Implement proper loading states

## Common Patterns
- Use React Hook Form for form handling
- Implement proper validation with Zod
- Use TanStack Query for API calls
- Follow the existing component structure
- Use the established routing patterns
